# Deployment Walkthrough: Avani Agro Foods

The Avani Agro Foods platform is now successfully deployed and live on Hostinger.

## Actions Taken

### 1. Local Build & Packaging
- Ran `npm run build` locally to generate optimized production assets.
- Compressed the `dist/` folder contents into a `deploy.zip` archive for easy uploading.

### 2. Manual Deployment
- Uploaded the production files to the Hostinger `public_html` directory.
- Removed conflicting WordPress files to ensure the React application takes precedence.

### 3. Routing Configuration
- Created a custom `.htaccess` file to handle Single Page Application (SPA) routing, ensuring that subpages like `/about`, `/contact`, and `/blog` load correctly without 404 errors.

## Verification Results

- **Home Page**: [avaniagrofoods.com](https://avaniagrofoods.com) is LIVE and verified.
- **Subpage Routing**: Verified that subpages (e.g., `/about`) resolve correctly to the React application.
- **SEO Elements**: Verified that Meta tags and Title tags are correctly appearing in search results.

## Final File Structure in `public_html`
- `assets/` (CSS/JS chunks)
- `index.html` (Main entry point)
- `sitemap.xml` (For search engines)
- `robots.txt` (For search engines)
- `.htaccess` (For routing)
- Various images (`sachin.png`, `report-cover.png`, etc.)

